const wchar_t szHelp[]=L"vana v1.1\r\nSite: https://github.com/Yuri213212/vana\r\nCopyright (C) 2020-2021 Yuri213212\r\nEmail: yuri213212@vip.qq.com\r\nLicense: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0\r\nhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/\r\n\r\nThis program analyzes wav file, and shows graph during playing.\r\nThe graph is to match tracker format to support musical dictation.\r\n\r\nThe bar at top is an image of the top of piano keybord.\r\nThe place with little red square is absolute C-4 by default.\r\nThe red line in the middle is the cursor pointing to current data.\r\n\r\nPress 'Load' button to load wav file.\r\nYou should set parameters properly in order to take musical dictation.\r\nThe default tempo is set by analyzing fourier series of power of input,\r\nit is not always accurate, but has significant reference value.\r\nChange range and press 'AutoSet' button to reanalyze tempo.\r\n\r\nUse vertical scroll bar or (page) up/down key to change position.\r\nUse horizontal scroll bar or left/right arrow key to change volume.\r\nPress alphabetic key to change transpose.\r\nPress 'Play' button or Enter key to play from the start of selected data,\r\nor to replay from the start of this playing.\r\nPress 'Pause' button to stop playing, with cursor unchanged.\r\nPress space key to toggle play/pause state.\r\nPress 'Stop' button or Esc key to stop playing, and reset cursor.";
